#### Phase 1: Epic Discovery

**Objective:** Generate unique epic ID and check for name conflicts

**Step 1.1: Find Existing Epics**

```
epic_files = Glob(pattern="devforgeai/specs/Epics/*.epic.md")

IF epic_files is empty:
  next_epic_id = "EPIC-001"
  epic_count = 0
ELSE:
  # Parse all epic IDs to find highest
  epic_ids = []

  FOR each epic_file in epic_files:
    Read(file_path=epic_file)
    Extract id from YAML frontmatter (pattern: "id: EPIC-(\d+)")
    epic_ids.append(extracted_number)

  highest_id = max(epic_ids)
  next_epic_id = f"EPIC-{highest_id + 1:03d}"  # Zero-padded (EPIC-001, EPIC-002, etc.)
  epic_count = len(epic_ids)
```

**Step 1.2: Check for Duplicate Epic Names**

```
epic_name = extract from conversation context "**Epic name:** (.*)" pattern

# Search for existing epic with same title (case-insensitive)
duplicates = Grep(
  pattern=f"title: .*{epic_name}",
  path="devforgeai/specs/Epics/",
  output_mode="files_with_matches",
  -i=true
)

IF duplicates found:
  # Read duplicate epic to get ID and details
  Read(file_path=duplicates[0])
  Extract existing_epic_id, status, created_date from YAML

  AskUserQuestion:
    Question: f"Epic named '{epic_name}' already exists ({existing_epic_id}, created {created_date}). How to proceed?"
    Header: "Duplicate epic name"
    Options:
      - label: f"Create new epic with same name ({next_epic_id})"
        description: "Allow duplicate names (different IDs distinguish them)"
      - label: f"Edit existing epic ({existing_epic_id})"
        description: "Update the existing epic instead of creating new one"
      - label: "Cancel and rename"
        description: "Provide a different epic name"
    multiSelect: false

  IF user selects "Edit existing":
    epic_id = existing_epic_id
    mode = "update"
    # Continue with editing existing epic (read current content, merge changes)

  ELSE IF user selects "Cancel":
    HALT: "Epic creation cancelled. Please provide a different epic name."

  ELSE:
    epic_id = next_epic_id
    mode = "create"
    # Continue with new epic creation
ELSE:
  epic_id = next_epic_id
  mode = "create"
```

**Output:**
- epic_id (EPIC-NNN)
- mode (create or update)
- epic_count (for summary reporting)

